  "prompt": "How do I get Pikachu as my first Pok\u00e9mon in Pok\u00e9mon GO?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon GO, Pikachu is not a starter Pok\u00e9mon by default. However, when you first start the game, you can actually choose Pikachu as your first Pok\u00e9mon with a little trick:\n\n1. When the game starts and you're presented with the initial three starter Pok\u00e9mon (Bulbasaur, Charmander, and Squirtle), do NOT select any of them.\n\n2. Walk away from these three Pok\u00e9mon multiple times.\n\n3. After walking away 4-5 times, Pikachu will spawn as an additional option.\n\n4. You can then select Pikachu as your first Pok\u00e9mon.\n\nThis method works for new players when they first start the game. If you've already chosen a starter Pok\u00e9mon, you'll need to catch Pikachu through normal gameplay methods like finding it in the wild or through eggs.",
